<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Subscription Cancelled - Idispatch Mobility</title>
</head>

<body style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #333; line-height: 1.6;">
    <div
        style="max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 20px; background: #fff6f6; border-radius: 10px; border: 1px solid #ffcccc;">

        <h2 style="color: #d9534f; text-align: center;">⚠️ Your Subscription Has Been Cancelled</h2>

        <p>
            Dear <%= userName %>,
        </p>

        <p>
            We’re sorry to see you go! 💔
            Your subscription to the <strong>
                <%= planName %>
            </strong> plan (Subscription ID: <%= subsctiptionId %>) has been cancelled.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 20px; color: #444;">📌 Cancellation Details</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Subscription ID:</strong>
                <%= subsctiptionId %>
            </li>
            <li><strong>Plan Name:</strong>
                <%= planName %>
            </li>
            <li><strong>Cancellation Date:</strong>
                <%= cancellationDate %>
            </li>
            <li><strong>Access Until:</strong>
                <%= endPeriod %>
            </li>
        </ul>

        <p style="margin-top: 20px;">
            You will continue to have access to all features of your plan until <strong>
                <%= endPeriod %>
            </strong>. After this date, your account will be downgraded to the free plan.
        </p>

        <p>
            We truly valued having you as part of the Idispatch Mobility family, and we’d love to welcome you back
            anytime. 💫
            If there’s anything we could improve to serve you better, please let us know — your feedback means the world
            to us. 🙏
        </p>

        <p>
            👉 Want to rejoin? You can easily reactivate your subscription at any time by logging into your account.
        </p>

        <p style="margin-top: 20px;">
            Wishing you all the best, <br>
            <strong>The Idispatch Mobility Team</strong>
        </p>

    </div>
</body>

</html>